  intro="Every photo your phone takes carries a hidden metadata packet called EXIF. It includes the GPS coordinates where the shot was taken, the exact time, your device model, and sometimes enough detail to identify your home or workplace. Most people have no idea. Here's what EXIF contains, where it leaks, and the ways to strip it before sharing."
  keyPoints={[
